{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccw3fgn7YdKF68nLnUAM4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Nice — race conditions in fixture setup are some of the nastiest to track down precisely because they're intermittent, so an afternoon is honestly a fair price. A file lock is a solid fix for shared-file contention.\n\nOne thing worth a quick sanity check while it's fresh: a lock serializes access, but if the underlying issue is that tests *share* a mutable file at all, the lock trades the race for a potential bottleneck (and can mask ordering assumptions rather than remove them). If it's cheap, giving each test its own temp file / unique path is often the more robust fix since it removes the sharing entirely. If per-test isolation isn't practical here, the lock is the right call.\n\nEither way, glad it's green now. Want me to do anything with it — e.g. look at the fixture code, or add a comment explaining the race so the next person doesn't \"optimize\" the lock away?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5123,"cache_read_input_tokens":16998,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5123},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"297dab3c-b3a9-4c96-8876-c336a52c593a","uuid":"6a0ce543-90b6-4a7e-8fda-9703d8e62c27","request_id":"req_011Ccw3fde6s5HB6NgcW2jy7"}
